saveConstruct

public void saveConstruct(org.langricr.mcmachina.construct.Construct construct)
Attempts to save a construct to the disk.
Creates the construct file to hold the information pertaining to a construct directly. Calls a ConstructSaveEvent with an optional related file to store additional information pertaining to a construct's data.
Cancelling will not alter either of the two files.

Parameters:
construct - The construct to be saved.

deleteConstruct

public void deleteConstruct(org.langricr.mcmachina.construct.Construct construct)
Attempts to delete the construct from the game.
If it is not can cancelled, it will delete the save file, remove the construct from the list and unhook all of it's listeners.

Parameters:
construct - The construct to be deleted.

destroyConstruct

public void destroyConstruct(org.langricr.mcmachina.construct.Construct construct)
Used to destroy a construct, if this event is not cancelled it will then attempt to delete the construct.
Called when a construct has a block removed from it that belongs to it's blueprint, cancelling will cancel the block from being destroyed.

Parameters:
construct - The construct to be destroyed
